    - "Theme: __bool__/__str__/__repr__ dict-presence (bool(x), str(x), repr(x))."
    - "All values False — struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __bool__, __str__, or __repr__ in its own __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not override bool/str/repr at the class level."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no bool/str/repr conversion defined in its own __dict__."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
